com.novartis.opensource.yada.format

Interface Converter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConverter, FileSystemResultJSONConverter, RESTResultDelimitedConverter, RESTResultJSONConverter, ResultSetResultDelimitedConverter, ResultSetResultHTMLConverter, ResultSetResultJSONConverter, ResultSetResultXMLConverter, SOAPResultXMLConverter

    public interface Converter
    The YADA API for formatting query results for insertion into Response objects.
    Since:
    0.4.0.0
    Author:
    David Varon

    • Field Detail

      • harmonyMap

        static final Object harmonyMap
        A (usually) JSONObject implementation of the Harmony Map Spec. As there are numerous JSON java implementations this object is stored as a generic Object

      • harmonizer

        static final Harmonizer harmonizer
        A utility class enabling remapping of result content

      • yqr

        static final YADAQueryResult yqr
        The container for results. This is useful in particular when harmonizing results, to store pre-processed headers separately and stitch results together in a subsequent step.
        Since:
        6.1.0

    • Method Detail

      • convert

        Object convert(Object result)
               throws YADAConverterException
        Intended to take raw results from a query and wrap or transform them into the proper format, including the mapping of fields based on provided harmonyMap specification
        Parameters:
        result - the raw query results
        Returns:
        the converted result
        Throws:
        YADAConverterException - when result conversion fails

      • convert

        Object convert(Object result,
             String colsep,
             String recsep)
               throws YADAConverterException
        Intended to take raw results from a query and wrap or transform them into the proper delimited format, including the mapping of fields based on provided harmonyMap specification
        Parameters:
        result - the raw query result
        colsep - the column delimiter
        recsep - the line delimiter
        Returns:
        the converted, delimited result
        Throws:
        YADAConverterException - when result conversion fails
